issue.title: dnnl ep fixes

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
-address https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/7155 where get_available_providers() wasn't working for DNNL EP.
-fix issue where libonnxruntime_providers_dnnl.so cannot locate libdnnl.so.1

body:
there was a bug impacting get_available_providers() for DNNL.
it doesn't return DNNLExecutionProvider even though it is enabled in the build.
when you actually create a session and do session.get_providers()  , it does return DNNLExecutionProvider

@jywu-msft You are right! I just checked with `session.get_providers()` and I did have DNNLExecutionProvider. Thanks!

As a side question: @waytrue17 and I are MXNet developers and we are working on MXNet's onnx export support. Would you suggest any other performance optimization except DNNL? We are targeting cpu and gpu for now
